{"Title": "Design of a 1 Tb/s superchannel coherent receiver", "Year": 2016, "Source": "J Lightwave Technol", "Volume": "34", "Issue": 6, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 1453, "PageEnd": 1463, "CitedBy": 49, "DOI": "10.1109/JLT.2016.2519260", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84963964152&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2016 IEEE.We describe the design of a trained and pilot-aided digital coherent receiver, capable of detecting a 1 Tb/s superchannel with a single optical front-end. Algorithms for receiver training are described, which calculate the equalizer coefficients, subchannel SNRs, and centroids of the transmitted constellations. Algorithms for pilot-aided operation are then described in detail, providing pilot-aided constant modulus equalization and joint carrier-phase estimation over several coherent subchannels. We demonstrate the detection of a superchannel with net bit rate in excess of 1 Tb/s with a single coherent receiver. An 11\u00d7 10 GBd DP-64QAM Nyquist superchannel is used, with 1.32 Tb/s gross bit rate.", "AuthorKeywords": ["Carrier phase estimation", "coherent detection", "LDPC", "superchannel"], "IndexKeywords": ["Carrier phase estimation", "Coherent detection", "Coherent receivers", "Constant moduli", "Equalizer coefficients", "LDPC", "Optical front-ends", "Superchannel"], "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 0, "EID": "2-s2.0-84963964152", "SubjectAreas": [["Atomic and Molecular Physics, and Optics", "PHYS", "3107"]], "AuthorData": {"35248788300": {"Name": "Millar D.S.", "AuthorID": "35248788300", "AffiliationID": "60003398", "AffiliationName": "Mitsubishi Electric Research Laboratories"}, "26658334600": {"Name": "Koike-Akino T.", "AuthorID": "26658334600", "AffiliationID": "60003398", "AffiliationName": "Mitsubishi Electric Research Laboratories"}, "36025704700": {"Name": "Pajovic M.", "AuthorID": "36025704700", "AffiliationID": "60003398", "AffiliationName": "Mitsubishi 